06:37.465 --> 06:39.506
- Meaning it only holds...
- Hi!

06:39.508 --> 06:41.713
Within the
confines of the code.

06:41.715 --> 06:42.925
Hi, excuse me.

06:44.340 --> 06:45.675
Are you Piet Carnell?

06:47.175 --> 06:49.713
- Yes, how do you...
- May I?

06:49.715 --> 06:51.463
It won't take long, I promise.

06:51.465 --> 06:53.673
I'm looking for a partner
for the term paper

06:53.675 --> 06:56.588
and Professor Karadimos told
me that you were available.

06:56.590 --> 06:57.423
Yeah?

06:57.425 --> 06:58.713
Yes,
I would love it if...

06:58.715 --> 07:03.463
No, um, uh, no, I
really need to get going.

07:03.465 --> 07:04.588
Of course!

07:04.590 --> 07:07.631
- For some, I have...
- So, what about the project?

07:07.633 --> 07:10.006
Yeah, I think you have
the wrong information

07:10.008 --> 07:12.131
because I already
have a partner.

07:12.133 --> 07:14.381
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

07:14.383 --> 07:16.550
Maybe another time
and have a nice day.

07:25.925 --> 07:28.131
Hello, Mr. Spengler.

07:28.133 --> 07:29.923
Right on time for
our little private chat.

07:29.925 --> 07:31.713
How are you doing, sweetheart?

07:31.715 --> 07:33.300
I'm fine, thank you.

07:35.008 --> 07:36.425
How do you like my outfit?

07:38.425 --> 07:39.425
Not too much?

07:40.633 --> 07:43.048
'Cause I know you like it
more casual, don't you?

07:43.050 --> 07:43.925
Sometimes.

07:46.008 --> 07:49.088
Alright, what
do you feel like today?

07:49.090 --> 07:52.588
You want me to show you
my new high heels?

07:52.590 --> 07:53.425
Sounds good.

07:54.675 --> 07:55.963
They're super fancy.

07:55.965 --> 07:59.506
I'll be right back.

08:09.758 --> 08:11.008
Who's there?

08:16.590 --> 08:17.507
Hi, Piet.

08:18.508 --> 08:19.338
Hey.

08:19.340 --> 08:21.548
Sorry for being so pushy.

08:21.550 --> 08:24.258
I kind of had the feeling
that I scared you off.

08:26.675 --> 08:28.508
What can I help you with?

08:29.715 --> 08:33.381
I read your last paper
and I thought it was great.

08:33.383 --> 08:35.173
So, if it's a possibility,

08:35.174 --> 08:37.090
I would really like
to work with you.

08:38.340 --> 08:39.549
You read my paper?

08:40.758 --> 08:41.673
What can I say?

08:41.674 --> 08:42.712
It's really good,

08:42.715 --> 08:44.965
especially your
counter-thesis to Ian Clark.

08:46.883 --> 08:47.716
Thank you.

08:48.716 --> 08:51.880
Um, you know, I already
have a partner, so...

08:51.882 --> 08:54.214
Look, I'm the new kid
and you don't know me,

08:54.216 --> 08:56.047
but I'm a fast learner.

08:56.049 --> 08:58.424
And I promise you won't
regret working with me.

09:06.882 --> 09:11.882
♪ I'll make the sunshine's
rays hot for you ♪

09:13.882 --> 09:15.339
♪ Every night ♪

09:15.341 --> 09:18.214
So, you do
classification of data sources.

09:18.216 --> 09:19.755
Okay.

09:19.757 --> 09:20.630
Alright.

09:20.632 --> 09:24.590
And chapter three,
the ghost machine?

09:25.425 --> 09:26.550
I'll do that.

09:27.550 --> 09:28.757
Okay, but what is it?

09:30.632 --> 09:32.590
It's part of
a theory of mine.

09:34.050 --> 09:35.425
Can you explain it to me?

09:38.591 --> 09:40.050
Okay, um...

09:41.632 --> 09:45.925
Imagine you, um, you had a tool

09:46.966 --> 09:51.966
that was able to move through
the internet like a ghost.

09:54.466 --> 09:57.130
Like a covert by proxy?

09:57.132 --> 09:58.382
Even more than that.

09:59.716 --> 10:03.464
Think IC reach,
just more powerful.

10:03.466 --> 10:07.048
You'd be able to access
everybody's accounts;

10:07.050 --> 10:11.132
banks, emails, social networks.

10:11.966 --> 10:13.214
Even beyond that you'd be able

10:13.216 --> 10:15.964
to access anybody's
computer, look inside

10:15.966 --> 10:19.298
their computer's hard drive
as if it was your own.

10:19.300 --> 10:24.132
The interesting question is;
if you had a tool like this

10:25.841 --> 10:28.216
and nobody knew about
it, would you use it?

10:30.800 --> 10:33.716
I guess everybody would
at least take a peek, right?

10:34.800 --> 10:37.423
But we both agree
this would be wrong?

10:37.425 --> 10:38.800
This would be a wrongdoing?

10:41.175 --> 10:42.589
Alright, so?

10:42.591 --> 10:47.050
So, the question is;
if getting away with it

10:48.007 --> 10:53.007
determines whether or not you're
gonna do something immoral.

10:56.091 --> 10:58.089
Well, I guess it's true,

10:58.091 --> 11:00.505
but it's not exactly
informatics.

11:00.507 --> 11:02.505
Why do you think this
should be in the paper?

11:02.507 --> 11:05.548
Because the entire
idea of digital traces

11:05.550 --> 11:08.423
comes with moral issues,
either for the one who collects

11:08.425 --> 11:11.007
the traces or the one
who leaves them behind.

11:12.675 --> 11:15.589
Control over traces
equals a lot of power.

11:15.591 --> 11:17.548
And the potential power
of a ghost machine

11:17.550 --> 11:20.673
would make anybody
feel untouchable,

11:20.675 --> 11:22.925
hence allowing them to act
immoral.

11:24.382 --> 11:28.382
But a wrongdoing, a
wrongdoing is a wrongdoing.

11:29.841 --> 11:33.883
Even though you had the
guarantee to get away with it.

11:36.300 --> 11:38.966
Piet, may I ask you
something personal?

11:40.425 --> 11:41.257
Okay.

11:42.675 --> 11:46.175
You are a great
guy and really smart.

11:47.175 --> 11:49.716
How come you hide
yourself away like this?

11:50.632 --> 11:52.215
I've never seen you in class.

11:54.757 --> 11:58.089
I just don't feel
comfortable around people.

11:58.091 --> 11:58.923
But how come?

11:58.925 --> 12:00.591
You don't seem
uncomfortable now.

12:02.257 --> 12:03.257
Well, I'm not now.

12:07.716 --> 12:08.923
Should we continue?

12:08.925 --> 12:11.300
It's a little strange
talking about this.

12:13.257 --> 12:17.255
Well, you know, I'm not
your advisor or anything,

12:17.257 --> 12:20.257
but maybe you should
challenge yourself a little?

12:41.050 --> 12:42.382
- Hello.
- Hello.

12:44.216 --> 12:46.880
Is the lasagna good today?

12:46.882 --> 12:48.050
Excuse me?

12:48.966 --> 12:51.380
Would the lasagna be
a good choice today?

12:51.382 --> 12:52.800
I don't eat here.

12:54.091 --> 12:54.925
Oh.

12:57.466 --> 13:00.133
That's a lovely shirt.

13:02.757 --> 13:04.714
That's the uniform.

13:04.716 --> 13:05.966
Everybody wears it.

13:09.050 --> 13:10.130
Right.

13:14.216 --> 13:15.050
Yeah.

13:18.591 --> 13:19.425
Yeah.

13:58.507 --> 14:00.505
Fourth floor.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.089
Door opening.

14:02.091 --> 14:03.630
Wait a minute.

14:03.632 --> 14:04.800
You like her, don't you?

14:05.716 --> 14:06.548
No.

14:07.382 --> 14:08.464
You're such a bad liar.

14:08.466 --> 14:09.714
What's her name?

14:09.716 --> 14:10.714
Why do you care?

14:10.716 --> 14:11.548
Come on, Piet.

14:11.550 --> 14:14.214
- What's her name?
- Klara.

14:14.216 --> 14:15.464
Now we're talking.

14:15.466 --> 14:17.383
So when can I meet
your new girlfriend?

14:18.841 --> 14:19.839
Piet!

14:19.841 --> 14:21.714
I wish I hadn't told you.

14:21.716 --> 14:23.508
No, you did the right thing.

14:24.507 --> 14:26.505
It's good to talk to your
friends about shit like that.

14:26.507 --> 14:27.880
So, how far did you get?

14:27.882 --> 14:30.300
Come on, did you
make out, hold hands?

14:33.841 --> 14:34.925
So nothing happened?

14:36.716 --> 14:40.548
It's just we get along
really, really great.

14:40.550 --> 14:41.798
You know?

14:41.800 --> 14:43.341
That's, that's good.

14:46.341 --> 14:50.589
It's just, it's just I
don't know how to, um...

14:50.591 --> 14:54.464
I don't know how to get
it, you know, to, um...

14:54.466 --> 14:55.383
Make a move.

14:57.257 --> 14:58.339
What?

14:58.341 --> 15:03.008
You need to, uh, establish
a physical connection.

15:05.300 --> 15:07.214
But, it's not like that.

15:07.216 --> 15:08.425
It is like that.

15:09.425 --> 15:11.214
Don't you think that would be

15:11.216 --> 15:12.880
a little aggressive
with the project?

15:12.882 --> 15:14.173
Forget about the project.

15:14.175 --> 15:16.255
Everybody knows you don't
need any help on this.

15:16.257 --> 15:18.130
You need more game.

15:18.132 --> 15:21.215
So if you ever wanna have sex,
then you gotta make a move.

15:24.550 --> 15:25.382
Thanks.

15:32.257 --> 15:33.798
Are you alright, Piet?

15:33.800 --> 15:34.632
Yeah.

15:36.966 --> 15:39.464
You seem a bit tense.

15:39.466 --> 15:41.133
No, I'm fine.

15:46.675 --> 15:51.632
Well, actually I feel
a bit tense myself.

15:53.300 --> 15:54.800
Should we take a break?

15:56.675 --> 15:58.173
Shouldn't we just
finish this first?

15:58.175 --> 16:00.048
Relax, it's almost done.

16:00.050 --> 16:01.300
Let's sit for a while.

16:02.632 --> 16:03.465
And...

16:06.132 --> 16:07.340
I brought you something.

16:10.341 --> 16:11.175
Oh.

16:26.757 --> 16:28.507
That's great stuff.

16:35.132 --> 16:37.132
Where do you
want to go in life, Piet?

16:41.966 --> 16:43.008
You're gonna laugh.

16:44.882 --> 16:47.798
But I want to make the
world a better place.

16:50.925 --> 16:52.548
Like Jesus?

16:52.550 --> 16:55.630
No, not like Jesus.

16:55.632 --> 16:57.715
Like, uh...

17:00.132 --> 17:02.550
Like a modern day Robinhood.

17:03.675 --> 17:05.964
A Robinhood who never
leaves Sherwood Forest.

17:05.965 --> 17:07.880
That would work, yeah.

17:07.882 --> 17:08.964
You're full of shit.

17:15.465 --> 17:17.505
What about you?

17:17.507 --> 17:18.839
Mother Superior?

17:21.049 --> 17:23.464
Believe it or not,
I have no clue.

17:24.508 --> 17:29.133
Before I got into informatics
I was into all kinds of stuff;

17:30.258 --> 17:33.633
traveling, music, architecture.

17:35.465 --> 17:37.881
Why didn't you
study any of that?

17:37.883 --> 17:39.799
I guess I didn't
have a real passion.

17:41.383 --> 17:45.088
All I know is,
whatever I'll end up doing,

17:45.090 --> 17:46.675
I won't be selling it cheap.

17:47.633 --> 17:50.258
For now, I'm just trying to
get the best CV possible.

17:52.758 --> 17:53.633
That's rational.

17:55.465 --> 17:57.007
Actually, it's a bit cynical.

17:58.090 --> 18:00.175
But it's a cynical
world out there.

18:02.925 --> 18:05.590
Why do you think I never
leave the Sherwood Forest?

18:10.800 --> 18:12.340
What do you live off, anyway?

18:14.715 --> 18:16.465
- Do you have a scholarship?
- No.

18:18.008 --> 18:18.841
I have money.

18:20.550 --> 18:21.425
Where from?

18:23.090 --> 18:25.382
From the company
I sold last year.

18:32.550 --> 18:34.088
It's true.

18:34.090 --> 18:36.465
It's true, I had a small
company and I sold it.

18:37.633 --> 18:39.300
It's not a joke,
it's not a joke.

18:41.258 --> 18:42.758
Hey, that's a good track.

18:43.590 --> 18:46.175
I didn't know that you were
into this kind of music.

18:48.925 --> 18:52.715
Well, when I was a teenager,

18:54.340 --> 18:57.257
my mother, she sent me to a
language school in England.

18:58.758 --> 19:03.548
And I had a Jamaican roommate
and we would smoke weed

19:03.550 --> 19:07.048
and listen to Roxy Music
all day long.

19:07.050 --> 19:08.173
Really?

19:08.175 --> 19:09.298
Wow!

19:09.300 --> 19:13.340
- Yeah, no.
- Hey, you!

19:20.758 --> 19:22.048
That'd be cool.

19:22.050 --> 19:26.756
♪ Shivers runnin'
down your spine ♪

19:26.758 --> 19:31.758
♪ You need a love that'll
shock you to the bones ♪

19:37.300 --> 19:38.883
Klara, it's done.

19:43.550 --> 19:44.383
Klara?

20:07.215 --> 20:09.132
Goodnight, sleep tight.

21:05.508 --> 21:07.131
Oh, good morning.

21:07.133 --> 21:10.550
Good morning to you, too.

21:11.465 --> 21:13.798
I completely
passed out.

21:13.800 --> 21:16.963
I hope the sofa wasn't
too uncomfortable.

21:16.965 --> 21:19.088
No, no, I'll live.

21:19.090 --> 21:20.506
I'm in a bit of a hurry.

21:20.508 --> 21:22.631
I gotta go and feed the birds.

21:22.633 --> 21:23.673
The birds?

21:23.675 --> 21:25.840
Yeah, two budgies.

21:26.675 --> 21:28.715
My mom hates them so
I took them with me.

21:30.508 --> 21:31.383
That's nice.

21:32.925 --> 21:37.588
Well, it was a
fun project with you.

21:37.590 --> 21:38.800
I enjoyed it a lot.

21:40.050 --> 21:40.883
Me, too.

21:42.175 --> 21:43.798
Yeah.

21:43.800 --> 21:44.758
Don't be stupid.

21:47.550 --> 21:49.173
Let's hang out sometime.

21:49.175 --> 21:50.506
Yeah.

21:50.508 --> 21:52.175
- Oh, uh, Klara, Klara?
- Yeah?

21:53.008 --> 21:57.006
Maybe now that we're finished
with the paper and all,

21:57.008 --> 22:01.506
um, I was thinking maybe
you, we could have,

22:01.508 --> 22:04.713
um, a dinner on Saturday?

22:04.715 --> 22:06.881
- Yeah, lovely, sure.
- Yeah?

22:06.883 --> 22:09.131
Why don't you come
over to my place for a change?

22:09.133 --> 22:09.963
Yeah?

22:09.965 --> 22:11.006
Yeah.

22:11.008 --> 22:11.925
That'd be nice.

22:28.633 --> 22:31.631
♪ I may not be
your kind of guy ♪

22:31.633 --> 22:35.173
♪ No, no, no, no, no, no ♪

22:35.175 --> 22:37.756
♪ What difference does it make ♪

22:37.758 --> 22:41.216
♪ No, no, no, no, no, no ♪

22:51.258 --> 22:52.383
Hello.

22:53.258 --> 22:54.466
Wow, look at you!

22:55.965 --> 22:57.882
Uh, I brought wine.

22:59.633 --> 23:01.006
Tempranillo.

23:01.008 --> 23:03.756
- From Catalonia.
- I know, fantastico!

23:03.758 --> 23:05.006
Well, come in.

23:05.008 --> 23:07.383
- You like red wine, right?
- Yes, I love it.

23:08.675 --> 23:10.256
Make yourself comfortable.

23:10.258 --> 23:12.216
I gotta finish this really
quick.

23:13.425 --> 23:15.383
- Before we get to the wine.
- Okay.

23:28.800 --> 23:30.963
So that's what
you use that for?

23:30.965 --> 23:32.423
Handy, ain't it?

23:32.425 --> 23:34.465
Yeah, I don't think
I ever used mine.

23:35.715 --> 23:38.963
On the one hand, she's
like my best friend,

23:38.965 --> 23:42.381
but on the other hand, oh,
my God, she's no needy!

23:42.383 --> 23:44.963
And, you know, I feel
kind of bad seeing her.

23:44.965 --> 23:45.800
I feel annoyed.

23:47.090 --> 23:48.338
I know I shouldn't say that.

23:48.340 --> 23:49.588
- I know it.
- No, no, no!

23:49.590 --> 23:51.881
I totally get it,
my mom's the same.

23:51.883 --> 23:54.256
Yeah, she lives less
than an hour from here.

23:54.258 --> 23:55.548
- Really?
- Really, and she didn't want

23:55.550 --> 23:58.383
me to go because she said
she was worried about me.

24:00.883 --> 24:04.383
I wish she would just,
I don't know,

24:06.215 --> 24:09.131
screw the mailman or something.

24:10.508 --> 24:12.423
It's actually not funny.

24:12.425 --> 24:14.008
Yes, it kind of is.

24:15.800 --> 24:17.300
You are a fun guy.

24:20.215 --> 24:21.463
Where are you going?

24:21.465 --> 24:22.798
We need more drinks.

24:22.800 --> 24:24.925
Okay, keep 'em coming.

24:28.383 --> 24:30.300
This stuff is the best.

24:31.215 --> 24:32.798
What is it?

24:32.800 --> 24:35.548
It's my favorite
Polish vodka.

24:35.550 --> 24:36.838
Okay.

24:36.840 --> 24:37.965
Polish vodka.

24:39.175 --> 24:41.090
Let's drink Bruderschaft.

24:41.925 --> 24:43.838
Bruderschaft, what?

24:43.840 --> 24:48.673
It means brotherhood in
German and it goes like this.

24:48.675 --> 24:50.631
- Now, bottom's up!
- Oh, all of it?

24:50.633 --> 24:51.675
Yes, quickly.

